Iowa's Area Education Agencies
July 23 at 5:00 PM ·

Are you interested in becoming a Substitute Teacher? Register now for a remote learning course! Learn more at http://ow.ly/q7vA50zA9Hi

The degree requirement to obtain a substitute authorization is changed from a bachelor’s degree to an associate’s degree or 60 semester hours through a regionally-accredited institution. The substitute authorization course is still required. All courses are online for a total of 20 hours. Choose any course that fits with your schedule!
text:
Iowa's Area Education Agencies
July 23 at 5:00 PM ·

Are you interested in becoming a Substitute Teacher? Register now for a remote learning course! Learn more at http://ow.ly/q7vA50zA9Hi

The degree requirement to obtain a substitute authorization is changed from a bachelor’s degree to an associate’s degree or 60 semester hours through a regionally-accredited institution. The substitute authorization course is still required. All courses are online for a total of 20 hours. Choose any course that fits with your schedule!

It's a Friday, so here is the change of plans from the state today...This week its football...

Below is a link to a release from the Iowa High School Athletic Association regarding a revision of the 2020 varsity football schedule due to COVID-19.

This revised plan was approved by the Board of Control on Friday. The IHSAA plans to release further fall season and sport-specific guidance next week.

https://www.iahsaa.org/football-2020-revised-schedule

This link is now available under the News tab on the IHSAA home page, on the News page, on the Football page, and will be shared via IHSAA social media.

More information on a schedule, Parent's/Senior Night, Homecoming and our Throwback Jersey game from GMG as we have the information.

post_text:
Welcome to GMG, Toree Benson!
Toree is a recent BFA graduate of The Dance Center of Columbia College Chicago. While living in Chicago the past four years she has taught at local studios, community centers, and high schools. Benson also has debut work on The Dance Center Stage, Meraki Dance Company Showcase, and others. In the summer of 2019, she traveled to Paris to perform, train, and teach at “Camping” an international dance festival. Post-graduation she has moved back to Iowa to grow the dance community. While continuing to educate at local dance studios, she is also excited to bring new experiences and grow the GMG dance team!

post_text:
Welcome to GMG Miss Campbell!

I'm Katie Campbell and I graduated from South Tama in 2019. I currently attend Mount Mercy University and am majoring in elementary education. I also played volleyball my freshman year at Mount Mercy. I started playing AAU as a 6th grader, and then started coaching with my mom when I was an 8th grader and have been coaching ever since while continuing to play. I hope to instill lifelong lessons and values this season alson with helping them reach their personal playing potential. I'm excited to be the assistant volleyball coach at GMG!

post_text:
Welcome to GMG Miss Haughey!

My name is Brycelyn Haughey, I graduated from South Tama in 2017. I then went to Kirkwood Community College and graduated with my AA in 2018. After Kirkwood I transferred to Mount Mercy University but got a job offer which required me to go full time so I transferred to Buena Vista in 2020. I am majoring in Elementary Education with endorsements in Strat 1, Strat 2, and in math. I am also getting my masters in Special Education. This coming fall I will start a para position at the GMG Secondary and am excited to start as the Varsity Volleyball Coach. I have played volleyball for 7 years at South Tama and coached for 5 years between South Tama AAU and Rapid Spikers out of Cedar Rapids.

post_text: No matter the circumstances we have Wolverines willing to lend a hand in service. #GMGPride
shared_text:
Iowa Veterans Home
May 17 at 3:22 PM ·

Wow! The generosity of our donors continues to amaze and blow us away. The first picture is of Jenny Allen from Rube's Steakhouse. She picked up the donated meat from Iowa Premium Beef in Tama and dropped off the beef to us. ❤️

The second picture was taken by Erin Murty (Ag Teacher at GMG schools). She coordinated this donation with Jon Surman- General Manager/VP from Iowa Premium in Tama (he is in the black jacket) and with the Mid Iowa Youth Beef Team (thus the youth). They arrived a few minutes later with a second donation from GMG Schools of 160# frozen beef from the school. Rob and Dawn from food service received this donation on behalf of IVH. Thank you all for donating your time sharing your giving spirits with us!!
text:
No matter the circumstances we have Wolverines willing to lend a hand in service. #GMGPride

Iowa Veterans Home
May 17 at 3:22 PM ·

Wow! The generosity of our donors continues to amaze and blow us away. The first picture is of Jenny Allen from Rube's Steakhouse. She picked up the donated meat from Iowa Premium Beef in Tama and dropped off the beef to us. ❤️

The second picture was taken by Erin Murty (Ag Teacher at GMG schools). She coordinated this donation with Jon Surman- General Manager/VP from Iowa Premium in Tama (he is in the black jacket) and with the Mid Iowa Youth Beef Team (thus the youth). They arrived a few minutes later with a second donation from GMG Schools of 160# frozen beef from the school. Rob and Dawn from food service received this donation on behalf of IVH. Thank you all for donating your time sharing your giving spirits with us!!

post_text:
GMG Staff Recipe Challenge.
Teachers and staff members are sharing recipes. Give it a try and make them. Would be a good time to add something new to the menu, then share pictures of your cooking on each post. We are looking for some creative, tasty fun. #GMGPride

Mr. Gargas' Sopapilla Cheesecake:

Preheat oven to 350

2 tubes of crescent rolls
1 1/2 cups sugar
1 tbsp vanilla
2 packages softened cream cheese
1 tsp cinnamon or more to taste
1/2 cup melted butter

Spread one can crescent rolls in an ungreased 9x13 pan.

Cream together cream cheese, 1 cup of the sugar, and the vanilla.

Spread the mixture onto the crescent rolls evenly.

Put the top layer of rolls on, pinching seams closed. Drizzle melted butter all over the top, then mix the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle evenly over all.

Bake at 350 for 30-35 minutes, cool at least 30 minutes, and serve warm.

2 tubes of crescent rolls

1/2 cup melted butter

Spread one can crescent rolls in an ungreased 9x13 pan.

Put the top layer of rolls on, pinching seams closed. Drizzle melted butter all over the top, then mix the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle evenly over all.

post_text:
Welcome to GMG! Hello!

My name is Madysen Wall. I am an Iowa State University Graduate, with a degree in Family and Consumer Sciences Education, as well as my Health Endorsement. I love traveling, trying new things, baking, reading, and watching documentaries. My family loves to be outside, so in the summertime, we spend lots of time camping and boating. I also love music, so concerts and live music are another favorite pastime for me. One of the many reasons I became an FCS Teacher is that I have a strong passion for helping students succeed. I want to be a positive influence and role model for my students. I also believe that FCS consists of the basic life skills that everyone will use throughout a lifetime.

I am so excited to be joining GMG Secondary School. In addition to teaching, I will also be joining as Football Cheer Coach and FCCLA Sponsor. I look forward to meeting all of my students and their families, and I look forward to creating a classroom where students feel at home! See you all soon, and GO WOLVERINES!

Welcome to GMG!
Aaron Kirkpatrick lives in Van Horne with his wife and two sons who are 2 and 8. He’s been in software development for the last 15 years. He has an associates degree in Electrical Engineering Technology and a bachelor’s degree in Mathematics. He works extensively with the FIRST Technology Challenge and grew to love teaching through working with the Benton Community robotics teams. In his spare time, he enjoys playing video games, reading science fiction, and tinkering with electronics. He is excited to join the math department at GMG and coach the Robotics team.

post_text:
A 2013 graduate from Wartburg College, Chas Beeler has been working in education for six years as both a musician, and a technologist. Chas has most recently served as the Assistant Band Director at Newton High School. Prior to that, he worked as the Technology Specialist for Berg Middle School, also in the Newton Community School District. He is looking forward to getting back to the small, tight knit atmosphere that GMG offers and providing opportunities for GMG’s students.

In his spare time, Chas is very active in several central Iowa communities. He currently serves as Director of Membership for the Des Moines Valley Region Sports Car Club of America and as an organizer for Idea Spin Newton. As a musician, Chas performs regularly with the Newton Community Theatre, Newton Municipal Band, and the Karl L. King Band of Fort Dodge.

If you’d like to learn more about Chas, you can visit his website at www.chaswbeeler.com .

Yesterday afternoon, our Individual Events Speech Team participated in the Iowa Star Conference Festival at North Tama. Everyone got a great practice before we head to Vinton for District on Saturday. In particular, we had four members who were honored with medals:

Joaquin Fitzsimmons: Gold for Improvisation

Angel Schewe: Bronze for Poetry (which she wrote herself)

Hallie Claussen: Bronze for Spontaneous Speaking

Kaci Krier: Silver for Storytelling

Great job to all! #GMGPride

post_text:
We would like to invite all GMG, Garwin, and Green Mountain Alumni that either played for or against Coach Gary Peterson to come and join us at the GMG High School on Saturday, Jan. 11th and honor Coach Peterson for his years of dedication to our community. We are pleased to announce that on this day we will be renaming our basketball floor, Coach Gary Peterson Court.
The ceremony will take place before our Varsity Girls game with BCLUW immediately following the conclusion of our JV Boys game in the upstairs Gym.
There will be a meet and greet in the lunchroom starting at 1 PM where our Wolverine Youth Basketball program will be putting on a chili luncheon. Please pass this along to as many people as you can think of as this should be an outstanding way to show Coach what he has meant to us as a teacher and leader in our community for so many years.

GMG Community:
Reminder:
We will have support available on Monday, today, from 9-3 at the Secondary School in Garwin to help support any students, family, friends or community members who may need assistance in dealing with the recent events with our students. Central Rivers AEA is providing personnel to listen and talk with you as you need. We will have teachers, counselors and support staff available as well.

Feel free to stop by and chat with friends, students, or be here as community and support, all are welcome.

If you need assistance in any way please reach out to us on social media via a message, email (nkleinmeyer@gmgschools.org), or phone (641-499-2005).

Central Rivers AEA is providing personnel to listen and talk with you as you need. We will have teachers, counselors and support staff available as well.

Since the Homecoming game, we have received many questions about the the throwback jerseys. The biggest one, "Are there any left for sale?" So we are going to open it up to the public to order. The cutoff date to order will be November 8, 2019 at 4:00 P.M. We will send the order off that evening in hopes of getting them before Christmas.

To ensure your order goes through, we will need the size, number, and payment. Checks can be made out to GMG Football.

Cost and size
Small - X Large $100
2XL & 3XL $110

Please contact Mr. Kleinmeyer with your order or with any questions, 641-499-2005, or nkleinmeyer@gmgschools.org

Wednesday: Coronation, 7:00 pm, Powder Puff Football, football jersey auction, and food provided by LSB to follow, with Senior Bonfire finishing off the night.

Saturday: Homecoming pictures by Stalzer's in the school lobby from 7-8:00 pm, Homecoming dance at the store from 8-11:00 pm.
